WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.300 align:middle line:90%


00:00:12.300 --> 00:00:14.855 align:middle line:84%
>> Come into a nice
upright seated posture.

00:00:14.855 --> 00:00:16.230 align:middle line:10%
And before we
close our eyes, I'm

00:00:16.230 --> 00:00:17.280 align:middle line:10%
just going to show
you what we're going

00:00:17.280 --> 00:00:18.609 align:middle line:10%
to be doing with our hands.

00:00:18.609 --> 00:00:20.400 align:middle line:10%
We're going to be
practicing Nadi Shodhana,

00:00:20.400 --> 00:00:22.140 align:middle line:10%
alternate nostril breathing.

00:00:22.140 --> 00:00:23.910 align:middle line:84%
And to do that, we're
going to take Vishnu

00:00:23.910 --> 00:00:25.380 align:middle line:90%
Mudra in your right hand.

00:00:25.380 --> 00:00:26.880 align:middle line:84%
Here I'm using my
left, but you're

00:00:26.880 --> 00:00:29.710 align:middle line:84%
going to be using my right,
so I'm just mirroring you.

00:00:29.710 --> 00:00:32.774 align:middle line:84%
We're going to block your
right nostril with your thumb

00:00:32.774 --> 00:00:35.190 align:middle line:84%
and you're going to block your
left nostril with these two

00:00:35.190 --> 00:00:36.090 align:middle line:90%
fingers.

00:00:36.090 --> 00:00:38.280 align:middle line:84%
Your left hand is going
to come into Chin Mudra,

00:00:38.280 --> 00:00:40.360 align:middle line:84%
these two fingers
together palm up.

00:00:40.360 --> 00:00:41.160 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:00:41.160 --> 00:00:43.980 align:middle line:90%
So now we can close our eyes.

00:00:43.980 --> 00:00:54.480 align:middle line:10%
Sit up nice and tall,
soften your belly,

00:00:54.480 --> 00:00:57.430 align:middle line:10%
and just begin with
three very long,

00:00:57.430 --> 00:01:01.180 align:middle line:10%
slow balanced breaths into
your abdomen expanding out.

00:01:01.180 --> 00:01:05.960 align:middle line:90%


00:01:05.960 --> 00:01:07.250 align:middle line:90%
Even exhale.

00:01:07.250 --> 00:01:08.570 align:middle line:90%
Gently draw your navel in.

00:01:08.570 --> 00:01:11.300 align:middle line:90%


00:01:11.300 --> 00:01:14.750 align:middle line:84%
And as you do this,
just taking notice.

00:01:14.750 --> 00:01:18.600 align:middle line:84%
Is your right nostril or your
left nostril a little bit

00:01:18.600 --> 00:01:19.400 align:middle line:90%
more open?

00:01:19.400 --> 00:01:22.350 align:middle line:90%


00:01:22.350 --> 00:01:29.710 align:middle line:84%
Just bringing awareness to your
nasal passages as you slowly,

00:01:29.710 --> 00:01:32.770 align:middle line:84%
equally breathe in and
out through the nose.

00:01:32.770 --> 00:01:35.320 align:middle line:90%


00:01:35.320 --> 00:01:36.120 align:middle line:90%
Nice.

00:01:36.120 --> 00:01:38.910 align:middle line:84%
One last long breath in
through both nostrils.

00:01:38.910 --> 00:01:40.220 align:middle line:90%
Let the belly expand out.

00:01:40.220 --> 00:01:43.340 align:middle line:90%


00:01:43.340 --> 00:01:44.140 align:middle line:90%
Exhale.

00:01:44.140 --> 00:01:47.230 align:middle line:84%
Gently draw the navel in,
completely emptying the lungs.

00:01:47.230 --> 00:01:52.080 align:middle line:84%
We always begin and end
with the left nostril.

00:01:52.080 --> 00:01:55.350 align:middle line:84%
So blocking your right
nostril, inhale slowly

00:01:55.350 --> 00:02:02.710 align:middle line:84%
